eBay Inc's PayPal plans First Job Cuts Since 2008 Financial Crisis-Reuters
Saturday, 13 Oct 2012 06:47pm EDT
Reuters reported that eBay Inc's payments division PayPal is planning to cut as much as 3% of its workforce as it looks to streamline its operations under new President David Marcus. The reductions are expected to total between 300 and 400 and be focused in product development, technology and marketing, the person said on condition of anonymity. PayPal has almost 13,000 employees.Â 
